  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "I would keep the `no-qualifying-elements` set to `false`. There are some edge cases when one might need to rely on them to enforce specific styles. Same for `nesting-depth`. It's hard to define an arbitrary depth for this as it can depends on a lot of things (eg nesting a modifier, then nesting a hover behaviour on the modifier etc.)",
    "created_at": "2017-11-13T09:34:00Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/2566#issuecomment-343862409",
